author: kfogel
msg: * www/project_faq.html, doc/user/lj_article.txt: Change some more
occurrences of "revision control" to "version control".
Patch by: zbrown
* www/variance-adjusted-patching.html: Same.  Also, add an original
datestamp, something I'd been meaning to get around to.  This is the
creation date reflected in our CVS repository and our ChangeLog, and
makes it clear for "prior art" purposes that the idea has been out
there for a while (probably since before this document, since I'm
sure I didn't think of it first).
This is an empty revision for padding.

author: philip
msg: Catch attempts to commit from multiple working copies.  One day we may
support this, but not yet.
* subversion/libsvn_client/commit.c (svn_client_commit):  Ensure all
targets are from the same working copy.
* subversion/tests/clients/cmdline/commit_tests.py (commit_multiple_wc): New
test.
